The paper deals with the construction and decoding of Space Time Block Codes (STBCs), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of various algebraic structures such as Clifford Unitary Weight Designs (CUWDs), Coordinate Interleaved Orthogonal Designs (CIODs), Cyclic Division Algebras (CDAs), and Crossed-Product Algebras (CPAs), which are topics in algebra and number theory (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the reduction of decoding complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also deals with the optimization of decoding algorithms, which is a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the application of STBCs in wireless communication systems, which is a topic in control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
